events.name: Future Fridays: Fairytales for the Future
events.description:
Fairytales are a way that societies use to remember traits that they value. They are also a way that we pass on social norms to our children. What are the stories that we grew up with as children? What stories might we be telling our grandchildren in the future?

Join us this Friday to explore what stories we might be telling in the future, and how we might tell those stories. If you are joining us, please reply to chewlin.kay@sl2square.org Come prepared to share one or two of your favorite childhood tales!
events.location: Sustainable Living Lab (SL2), 111 Middle Rd, Unit 01-02, Singapore 188969
